The paper deals with graph algorithms and their implementation in models of computation with sublinear space usage and constrained access to input data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), and Graph Theory (cs.GT). Among these categories, cs.DS and cs.DC are the most likely as the paper deals with algorithms and their implementation in resource-constrained settings. The use of linear sketches and MapReduce also suggests that the paper may belong to cs.DM and cs.GT, while the analysis of the algorithm's approximation factor may indicate that it belongs to cs.CC.
